&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Production Coordinator - Audio is responsible for the setup, operation, and maintenance of the venue’s sound system, ensuring high-quality audio for live events. This role also supports A/V and PA systems, assists with stage and equipment maintenance, and serves as a key liaison between vendors, artists, and crews to ensure seamless event execution.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for set up, operation and maintenance of venue sound system. Operate sound system during shows and confirm that microphones and speakers are&amp;nbsp;functioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as back-up for A/V and PA systems. Responsible for set up, operation and maintenance of A/V system. Maintain the public announcement system in optimal working condition. Operate PA during shows if Sound Engineer is absent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Venue maintenance including lighting, sound, stage and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for set up and break down of equipment on stage. Load/unload equipment from trucks and set up equipment according to stage design while ensuring safety requirements are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;May be responsible for production and operations aspects including vendor end-to-end onsite set up: exhibitor registration and follow-up survey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary liaison between vendors, artists, sounds crews, and property management companies in execution of shows and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience with live sound production, A/V systems, and stage setup preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in operating and maintaining audio, PA, and A/V systems; knowledge of stage equipment and lighting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift and transport equipment, work in a fast-paced environment, and perform stage maintenance tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to coordinate with artists, vendors, and crew members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to troubleshoot and resolve technical issues under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payscale: &lt;/strong&gt;$22.00 - $22.50&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This position is not eligible for a bonus under the current bonus plan requirements.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part-time: &lt;/strong&gt;This position may be eligible for benefits (ACA qualification).&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
